Last Week, through our presenter Dorothy Santos, about twine, creative process, and self exploration.
The appropriately named title, of "Allowing yourself to Wander and Wonder", befittingly captures all of this and more.
Having done some previous lectures and speaking for the class before, Professor Santos, begins with defining herself.
i.e. through some of the titles or labels that they have accumulated throughout her lifetime, highlighting the ones most impactful to them.
I really like this, whether through exercise or just having this idea ready at any time. 
Illustrating the idea of authenticity and keeping in mind your roots constantly, whenever self expression must be done.
Going further, prof. Santos introduces the concept of Personal Ecology inspired from Mimi Lok.
In which, on a hypothetical square, each corner is given a catergory: people, places, values, and events, and at the center being you.
You would then approporiately put the coinciding label or individual in those places.
Furthermore, you would then draw complements and constraints to each of those labels. i.e. which label affects another label.
This idea of self stock, is only honestly a really interesting method of self reflection. 
Either during a period of chaos, or artisit block, I think this would be an effective tool in the repretoire of any artist or creative.
Closing off the slides, professor Santos introduces us to twine.
Being another medium to code, I'm sure there are more ways to use this but I'd like the direciton of "choose your own adventure type of story".
Something possibly for an off-ramp project.
Overall, a very productive week 2 despite everything going on.
